item.description:
@Ddragonimp wrote:

open up the directory

“My Computer”
Now go to the C: Drive (could say Local C)
Go to the Directory Program Files
Go to the Directory Java
Go to the Directory jdk1.6.0_22

If the folder doesnt exist… change jk1.6.0_22 to the file name that does exist

if your on windows 7 (i think or vista)

Loveandpower:

try adding (x86) after program files

If none of that works… Install java JDK
